        hack: {
          memory: "DNA Center = Catalyst Center (2023 rebrand) = on-prem network-wide manager. Manages EVERYTHING Cisco (switches, routers, WLCs, APs, SD-WAN). Contrast: WLC = wireless only. Meraki = cloud-managed. DNA Center = on-prem, all infrastructure. The core of Cisco's Intent-Based Networking (IBN).",
          practice: "Cisco dCloud (free for partners/students) has DNA Center demo sandboxes. Spend 30 minutes clicking through the UI: discover devices, view topology, navigate the four tabs (Design, Policy, Provision, Assurance). This UI tour cements what DNA Center DOES vs just memorizing the name.",
          effort: "low",
          meta: "Jeremy's IT Lab Days 60-61 (Network Automation) cover DNA Center/Catalyst Center. Wendell Odom OCG Chapter 29. Exam question: 'what Cisco platform provides centralized on-prem management for the entire network (not just wireless)?' → DNA Center / Catalyst Center."
        }
